ntlmv2.description: NTLMv2 challenge-response hashes from biglunchcorp.com domain. Generated with realistic North American names and password patterns (5-19 chars, mixed case, digits, special characters). Ideal for practicing NetNTLMv2 attacks.

md5.description: Common password MD5 hashes. Fast hash type (~60 GH/s on modern GPUs). Good for beginners learning hashcat basics.

md5crypt.description: Unix md5crypt hashes ($1$ format). Slow hash with salt (~30 MH/s). Common in older Linux systems (/etc/shadow).

sha256.description: Raw SHA-256 hashes. Medium speed (~8 GH/s). Common in web applications and custom authentication systems.
